  "2026-07-07T22:45:27.677Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: post-review lifecycle fix now stamps closed_at even if the update mutation helper is exercised without the public update-to-close auto-route. Added a direct helper regression in tests/unit/commands/update-command.spec.ts and reran the focused update suite plus full coverage; coverage remains 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-07T23:24:54.807Z",claude-code-agent,"Review follow-up evidence: hardened closed_at lifecycle stamping for the direct update mutation helper so missing and explicit null closed_at values both receive a close timestamp when status moves to closed, with focused regression coverage in tests/unit/commands/update-command.spec.ts and full coverage re-run passing 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-08T00:36:43.909Z",claude-code-agent,"Review follow-up evidence: reopened legacy items with closed_at=null now clear the property and record closed_at in changed_fields on direct update helper reopen, matching the lifecycle invariant that active items should not carry closure timestamps."
